In the INTEREST OF: T.J.-A. Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
T.A., Appellant. WD 81749 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: March 26, 2019 Edward E. Moore, Kansas City, for Respondent. Mitchell J. Widener, Co-counsel for Respondent. Tracey T. Chappell, for Appellant. Before Division Two: Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Presiding Judge, Alok Ahuja, Judge and Gary D. Witt, Judge ORDER PER CURIAM:

T.A. appeals the trial court's judgment terminating his parental rights to his minor child, T.J.-A. Finding no error, we affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
